The paper deals with a variant of the Feedback Vertex Set problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The problem involves deleting vertices or edges from a full binary tree, which is a data structure studied in the field of data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also establishes that the problem is FPT (fixed-parameter tractable) by the standard parameter, which is a topic studied in the field of parameterized complexity (cs.DM). Finally, the paper deals with the hardness of the problem, which is a topic studied in the field of graph theory (cs.GT).
